abstract.para: The current system of permanent sample plots (PSP) in the Cedar River Watershed (CRMW) was established to monitor the development of forest vegetation communities under the Habitat Conservation Plan. The sample was designed to represent the distribution of forest types in the watershed, to provide guidance for forest restoration, and to assess the effectiveness of restoration management.

project.title: Long-Term Forest Monitoring

personnel.organizationName: City of Seattle, Seattle Public Utilities

project.abstract: Longterm forest inventory [N54504] Based on the evaluations of standard forest inventory and secondary forest attribute data, and augmentation of the forest and habitat inventory described in the elements above, the City will design and conduct a longterm program of sampling and monitoring to update the forest and habitat inventory periodically over the full term of the HCP. The cost of this program will be up to $18,750 for design in HCP years 15, up to $62,600 in HCP years 610, up to $42,500 in HCP years 1115, up to $37,500 in HCP year interval 1620, up to $75,000 in each HCP year intervals 2130 and 3140, and up to $82,500 in HCP year interval 4150, for a total cost of $393,850.Field verification [N54504: note that this gets tracked with “Longterm forest inventory”] The City will complete field verification of habitat classifications of forested and nonforested polygons in the watershed GIS that is not accomplished as part of the four program elements above. The cost of this program will be up to $56,220 in HCP years 15.

codeDefinition.definition: trees above the highest continuous canopy

attribute.attributeDefinition: Description of measured tree's crown condition from status in the stand. 1) ISO = Isolated - tree crownss receive full light from above and all sides, 2) DOM = Dominant - trees with crwons that extend above the general level of the trees immediately around the measured trees, 3) CO = Codominant - trees with crowns forming the general level of the trees immediately around the measured trees, 4) INT = Intermediate - trees with crowns below, but extending into, the general level of the trees immediatley around the measured trees, and 5) OT = Overtopped - trees with crowns entirely below the general level of the trees around the measured trees, receiving no direct light rom either above or form the sides.
Length of live crown divided by total measured tree height multiplied by 100. Length of live crown = Total height - Height to crown. % Live Crown = (Length of live crown/Total height) x 100
Refer to Appendix, Table 1. for Damage codes and descriptions for live trees >5.0 inches DBH
